fr:tree.fr:mainmatter:
Given a morphism 
 f_{\sharp } : E \to  D, 
it induces a morphism of locally distributed spaces
 (f,f^{\sharp }) : \operatorname {Spec} D \to  \operatorname {Spec} E, 
where the underlying continuous map f sends a prime filter in D to its preimage under f_{\sharp }. This way, we have that for any e\in  E,
 f^{-1}(O_e) = \{x\in \operatorname {Spec} D\mid e \in  f_{\sharp }^{-1}(x)\} = \{e\in \operatorname {Spec} D\mid f_{\sharp } e \in  x\} = O_{f_{\sharp } e}. 
Hence on e\in  E, the induced map is the canonical map induced by f^*,

\usepackage {tikz-cd}\usepackage {quiver}
  \begin {tikzcd}
    \mathcal  O_E(1) \cong  E \ar [r, "f_{\sharp }"] \ar [d, two heads] & D \cong  \mathcal  O_D(1) \ar [d, two heads] \\ 
    \mathcal  O_E(e) \cong  E/e \ar [r, dashed, "f_{\sharp }"'] & D/f_{\sharp } e \cong  \mathcal  O_D(f_{\sharp } e)
  \end {tikzcd}


On each stalk x\in \operatorname {Spec} D, we have
 f^{\sharp }_x : (f^*\mathcal {O}_{E})_x \cong  \mathcal {O}_{E,fx} \cong  E/fx \to  D/x \cong  \mathcal {O}_{D,x} 
which is t-conservative, because it arises as the following factorisation,

\usepackage {tikz-cd}\usepackage {quiver}
  \begin {tikzcd}
    E \ar [r, "f_{\sharp }"] \ar [d, two heads] & D \ar [d, two heads] \\ 
    E/f_{\sharp }^{-1}(x) \ar [r] & D/x
  \end {tikzcd}

Given a morphism 
 f_{\sharp } : E \to  D, 
it induces a morphism of locally distributed spaces
 (f,f^{\sharp }) : \operatorname {Spec} D \to  \operatorname {Spec} E, 
where the underlying continuous map f sends a prime filter in D to its preimage under f_{\sharp }. This way, we have that for any e\in  E,
 f^{-1}(O_e) = \{x\in \operatorname {Spec} D\mid e \in  f_{\sharp }^{-1}(x)\} = \{e\in \operatorname {Spec} D\mid f_{\sharp } e \in  x\} = O_{f_{\sharp } e}. 
Hence on e\in  E, the induced map is the canonical map induced by f^*,

\usepackage {tikz-cd}\usepackage {quiver}
  \begin {tikzcd}
    \mathcal  O_E(1) \cong  E \ar [r, "f_{\sharp }"] \ar [d, two heads] & D \cong  \mathcal  O_D(1) \ar [d, two heads] \\ 
    \mathcal  O_E(e) \cong  E/e \ar [r, dashed, "f_{\sharp }"'] & D/f_{\sharp } e \cong  \mathcal  O_D(f_{\sharp } e)
  \end {tikzcd}


On each stalk x\in \operatorname {Spec} D, we have
 f^{\sharp }_x : (f^*\mathcal {O}_{E})_x \cong  \mathcal {O}_{E,fx} \cong  E/fx \to  D/x \cong  \mathcal {O}_{D,x} 
which is t-conservative, because it arises as the following factorisation,

\usepackage {tikz-cd}\usepackage {quiver}
  \begin {tikzcd}
    E \ar [r, "f_{\sharp }"] \ar [d, two heads] & D \ar [d, two heads] \\ 
    E/f_{\sharp }^{-1}(x) \ar [r] & D/x
  \end {tikzcd}

fr:mainmatter.html:p:
\operatorname {Spec} is the right adjoint to the global section functor

  \usepackage {tikz-cd}\usepackage {quiver}
  \begin {tikzcd}
    {\mathbf {DL}^{\mathrm {op}}} & \mathbf {Top}_{\mathbb  D}
    \arrow [""{name=0, anchor=center, inner sep=0}, "\mathrm {Spec}"', curve={height=18pt}, from=1-1, to=1-2]
    \arrow [""{name=1, anchor=center, inner sep=0}, "\Gamma "', curve={height=18pt}, from=1-2, to=1-1]
    \arrow ["\dashv "{anchor=center, rotate=-90}, draw=none, from=1, to=0]
  \end {tikzcd}


  identifying \mathbf {DL}^{\mathrm {op}} as a reflective subcategory of \mathbf {Top}_{\mathbb {D}}.

Let (X,\mathcal {O}_{X}) be a locally distributed space and D a distributive lattice. Given
   f_{\sharp } : D \to  \Gamma \mathcal {O}_{X}, 
  we construct a morphism of locally distributed spaces
   (f,f^{\sharp }) : (X,\mathcal {O}_{X}) \to  (\operatorname {Spec} D,\mathcal {O}_{D}). 
  The map f : X \to  \operatorname {Spec} D can be constructed as follows,

  \usepackage {tikz-cd}\usepackage {quiver}
    \begin {tikzcd}
      D \ar [dr, dashed, "f^{-1}"'] \ar [r, "f_{\sharp }"] & \Gamma \mathcal  O_X \ar [d, "=1"] \\ 
      & \Gamma \Omega _X
    \end {tikzcd}


  Since \mathcal {O}_{X} is local, by Remark  the composite is a distributive lattice morphism, thus produces a continuous function f : X \to  \operatorname {Spec} D by Proposition . Concretely, for any x\in  X we have
   fx = \{p\in  D\mid x \models  f_{\sharp }(p)\}. 
  In other words, D/fx is the (pro-open,t-conservative) factorisation of D \to  \Gamma \mathcal {O}_{X} \to  \mathcal {O}_{X,x}

  \usepackage {tikz-cd}\usepackage {quiver}
    \begin {tikzcd}
      D \ar [d, two heads] \ar [r, "f_{\sharp }"] & \Gamma \mathcal  O_{X} \ar [d] \\ 
      D/fx \ar [r] & \mathcal {O}_{X,x}
    \end {tikzcd}


  Here D/fx is local since \mathcal {O}_{X,x} by assumption is local and D/fx \to  \mathcal {O}_{X,x} is t-conservative. Hence by Proposition  fx is indeed a prime filter.

We then construct a morphism of distributive lattices f^{\sharp } : f^*\mathcal {O}_{D} \to  \mathcal {O}_{X}. Equivalently, this can be described as a compatible family of maps
   f_{\sharp } : \mathcal {O}_{D}(p) \cong  D/p \to  \mathcal {O}_{X}(f^{-1} p). 
  Compatibility means the following diagramme commutes,

  \usepackage {tikz-cd}\usepackage {quiver}
  \begin {tikzcd}
    D \ar [d, two heads] \ar [r, "f_\sharp "] & \mathcal  O_{X}(X) \ar [d, "(-)|_{f^{-1} p}"] \\
    D/p \ar [r, "f_\sharp "'] & \mathcal {O}_{X}(f^{^{-1}} p)
  \end {tikzcd}


  It then suffices to show that f_{\sharp }(p)|_{f^{-1}(p)} = 1. This holds, since by construction f^{-1}(p) is the subspace \{x\mid x \models  f_{\sharp }(p)\}. This being a local morphism follows immediately from the factorisation defining fx.

For any distributive lattice D, \operatorname {Spec} D is spectral. This gives us a functor
 \operatorname {Spec} : \mathbf {DL}^{\mathrm {op}} \to  \mathbf {Spec} 
from distributive lattices to spectral spaces.
